        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 28 at 4:38PM MDT until July 28 at 5:30PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>SVRTFX

The National Weather Service in Great Falls has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Meagher County in central Montana...
Southwestern Judith Basin County in central Montana...

* Until 530 PM MDT.

* At 438 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles east of
White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Checkerboard.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
